pets.name: Grayhound
pets.description: Hi, I am JoJo – a 2 year old spayed Beagle that is looking for a place to crash.

pets.name: Beagle
pets.description: Ben is a 2 year old spayed Beagle looking for a quiet home with lots of love to give.

pets.name: Labrador Retriever
pets.description: Did you know that I have been considered a Frisbee champion for my mad fetch skills? If you love your Frisbee as much as I love mine, you should hit me up so we can be a champion team.

pets.name: American Staffordshire Terrier
pets.description: I may not be winning any fetch awards, but I will definitely win over your heart with my mad snuggling skills. If a night of snack, snuggling and sitcoms is your thing – we may be a perfect match.

pets.name: Basset Hound
pets.description: I am a big dufus who can sometimes forget just how big I am and I would not want to mow down your little ones, so a home with adults or older kids might be best.

pets.name: Abyssinian
pets.description: The Abyssinian is often a colorful cat with a distinctly ticked coat, medium in size and regal in appearance; lithe, hard and muscular, showing eager activity and lively interest in their surroundings. They are often well balanced temperamentally and physically.

pets.name: American Shorthair
pets.description: The American Shorthair is a true breed of working cat. The general effect is that of a strongly built, well balanced, symmetrical cat with conformation indicating power, endurance, and agility.

pets.name: Bengal
pets.description: The Bengal is a domestic cat that has physical features distinctive to the small forest-dwelling wildcats, and with the loving, dependable temperament of a family pet. As such, some characteristics in the appearance of the Bengal are distinct from those found in other domestic cat breeds.

pets.name: British Shorthair
pets.description: The British Shorthair is a compact, well-balanced, and powerful cat, with a short, very dense coat. They often convey an overall impression of balance and proportion in which no feature is exaggerated.

pets.name: Devon Rex
pets.description: The Devon Rex is a breed of unique appearance. The breed’s large eyes, short muzzle, prominent cheekbones, and huge, lowset ears create a characteristic elfin look. A cat of medium fine frame, the Devon is well covered with soft, wavy fur. The fur is of a distinctive texture, as the mutation that causes its wavy coat is cultivated in no other breed.
